The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to detect discrete events in continuous video, specifically in the context of sports. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also indicates that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with signal processing and analysis, which could place it in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of different architectures for the problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
